Package camzup.core

Interface ISvgWritable

All Known Implementing Classes:
Curve2, CurveEntity2, ImageEntity2, Mesh2, MeshEntity2, TextEntity2
public interface ISvgWritable
Maintains consistent behavior between classes which support creation of an SVG file.

  • Field Summary

    Fields 
    Modifier and Type Field Description
    static float DEFAULT_HEIGHT
    Default height of an SVG view box, 512.0f.
    static float DEFAULT_ORIGIN_X
    Default origin x of a 'camera' transform in an SVG, expressed as a ratio in [0.0, 1.0].
    static float DEFAULT_ORIGIN_Y
    Default origin y of a 'camera' transform in an SVG, expressed as a ratio in [0.0, 1.0].
    static java.lang.String DEFAULT_STR_CAP
    Default stroke cap to use when rendering to an SVG, "round".
    static java.lang.String DEFAULT_STR_JOIN
    Default stroke join to use when rendering to an SVG, "round".
    static float DEFAULT_WIDTH
    Default width of an SVG view box, 512.0f.
    static java.lang.String DEFAULT_WINDING_RULE
    The default fill rule, or winding rule, from the enumeration "evenodd" and "nonzero".
    static int FIXED_PRINT
    The default number of decimal places to print real numbers in an SVG, 4.

    • toSvgElm

      default java.lang.String toSvgElm()
      Renders this object as a string containing an SVG element.

      the SVG string

    • toSvgElm

      java.lang.String toSvgElm​(float zoom)
      Renders this object as a string containing an SVG element.

      Stroke weight is impacted by scaling in transforms, so zoom is a parameter. If nonuniform zooming is used, zoom can be an average of width and height or the maximum dimension.
      Parameters:
      zoom - scaling from external transforms
      Returns:
      the SVG string

    • toSvgString

      java.lang.String toSvgString()
      Renders this object as an SVG string. A default material renders the mesh's fill and stroke. The background of the SVG is transparent.
      Returns:
      the SVG string

    • toSvgString

      default java.lang.String toSvgString​(float xOrigin, float yOrigin, float xScale, float yScale, float viewWidth, float viewHeight)
      Renders this object as an SVG string. A default material renders the mesh's fill and stroke. The background of the SVG is transparent. The width and height inform the view box dimensions. The origin is expected to be in unit coordinates, [0.0, 1.0] ; it is multiplied by the view box dimensions.
      Parameters:
      xOrigin - the origin x
      yOrigin - the origin y
      xScale - the scale x
      yScale - the scale y
      viewWidth - the width
      viewHeight - the height
      Returns:
      the SVG string

    • toSvgString

      default java.lang.String toSvgString​(Vec2 origin, Vec2 scale, Vec2 dim)
      Renders this curve as an SVG string. A default material renders the mesh's fill and stroke. The background of the SVG is transparent. The width and height supplied form both the view box dimensions, the translation and the scale of the shape.
      Parameters:
      origin - the origin
      scale - the scale
      dim - the dimensions
      Returns:
      the SVG string
